const pipe = await pipeline('image-text-to-text', 'onnx-community/Florence-2-base-ft');
const output = await pipe(
  'https://huggingface.co/datasets/Xenova/transformers.js-docs/resolve/main/cats.jpg',
  'Describe this image in detail'
);
console.log(output); // [{ generated_text: '...' }]
```

Also verify:
- TypeScript/JSDoc types are complete (typedef, callback, pipeline type alias)
- `pipeline('image-text-to-text')` with no model falls back to `"onnx-community/Florence-2-base-ft"`
- The class is exported and importable: `import { ImageTextToTextPipeline } from '@huggingface/transformers'`
- Existing pipelines are unmodified

